Swift Notes:

-exclamation points on C types states they are ready for use
-Use swift features such as type properties rather than C based modifying 
 functions(ex. Int.max.bigEndian vs. CFSwap...)
-Core Audio types containing Ref are valid, Core Founation types however have
 removed the suffix
-Swift functions can alternatively be written as closures
-Variables that have no initial value but whose memory will be accessed must be
 declared with an exclamtion point(!)
